<title>DocGen - Documentation</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/css/main.css">
</head>
<body style="padding:20px;max-width:600px;margin:0 auto">
<a href="/app" class="back">← Back</a>
<h1>DocGen Setup Guide</h1>

<h2 style="color:#a78bfa;margin-top:25px">1. Install</h2>
<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO.git
cd Dokle
pip install -r requirements.txt</code></pre>

<h2 style="color:#a78bfa;margin-top:25px">2. Run</h2>
<pre><code>python main.py
# Open http://127.0.0.1:5000</code></pre>

<h2 style="color:#a78bfa;margin-top:25px">3. CLI Commands</h2>
<pre><code>python cli.py analyze app.py
python cli.py generate src/
python cli.py github user/repo</code></pre>

<h2 style="color:#a78bfa;margin-top:25px">4. Docker</h2>
<pre><code>docker build -t docgen .
docker run -p 5000:5000 docgen</code></pre>

<h2 style="color:#a78bfa;margin-top:25px">5. Install as App</h2>
<p>Open in Chrome → Menu → Add to Home Screen</p>

<h2 style="color:#a78bfa;margin-top:25px">Links</h2>
<p><a href="https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO">GitHub Repository</a></p>
</body>
</html>
